    "Further investigation is warranted to validate this mechanism and explore alternative compensatory processes, such as the formation of oxygen vacancies or phase segregation, which could similarly address the observed lattice strain.In addition to structural, morphological and vibrational characterizations, Nyquist plot analysis was performed by impedance spectroscopy on BiFeO 3 samples with precursor ratios of 55: to the semicircle equation:(Z ′ -h) 2 + (Z ′′ -k) 2 = r 2, where (h, k) is the center, r is the radius and f max is the frequency at the maximum of the arc.",
    "These fitted parameters are reported in Table 1.",
    "1/(2πf max R p)), while the semicircle centres (h, k) yield the series resistance (R s = h -r).",
    "Since all semicircles are depressed (k < 0, centre below the real axis), the degree of depression was quantified using the geometric angle ϕ = arcsin |k| r, which directly relates to the Cole-Cole stretch parameter.",
    "The corresponding constant-phase-element (CPE) exponent was then calculated as n = 1 -2ϕ π (or equivalently n = 1 -2ϕ/180 • when ϕ is in degrees), ensuring full consistency with a nonideal representation (R p ∥ CPE) [45]."
